  "texts": [
    "To evaluate our method's robustness across diverse realworld editing scenarios, we additionally constructed a dataset of 200 image-prompt pairs from LAION [40] using Claude's multimodal API 3.",
    "The dataset covers five editing categories: Facial Expression Change, Object Addition, Object Removal, Pose Transformation, and Background Replacement, with prompts automatically generated based on image content.Through this varied set of prompts, we aimed to assess our method's effectiveness across a wide range of potential image manipulation scenarios.",
    "E. Image Quality Assessment (IQA)To quantitatively assess the quality of the edited images preand post-attack, we employed five different IQAs:• Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio (PSNR): provides insight into the overall distortion introduced.foot_3 • Fréchet Inception Distance (FID): offers a measure of the perceptual quality and generation diversity [41].foot_4 • Structural Similarity Index (SSIM): captures changes in local patterns of pixel intensities [42].foot_5 • Learned Perceptual Image Patch Similarity (LPIPS): measures human perceptual similarities [34].foot_6 • Aesthetic Color Distance Metric (ACDM): evaluates the overall color consistency [43], [44].",
    "8 F. Evaluation ProtocolSince baselines serve different objectives, for a comprehensive performance evaluation, we employ two distinct approaches.",
    "for methods subject to Objective 1, we compute IQAs between clean images and edited adversarial samples, represented as IQA(x, f (x adv))."
